description: From translingual Vireo (genus name), from Latin vireō (“I am green”).

entries.meaning: Any of a number of small insectivorous passerine birds, of the genus Vireo, that have grey-green plumage.
examples: The voices of male vireos are a constant in the spring woodland, providing background music to the longer, prettier songs of tanagers and thrushes. Vireos tend to sing in bursts interrupted by short or long pauses.

entries.meaning: Any bird of the family Vireonidae, which includes vireos, shrike-vireos, greenlets and peppershrikes.
examples: The vireos are slim grayish green birds that stay high up in the trees most of the time.
